cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.HC, cs.CL 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it introduces a reinforcement learning framework to optimize long-term user engagement in recommender systems. It also involves the use of a Q-Network and an S-Network, which are commonly used in deep reinforcement learning. 

It could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as recommender systems are often used in information retrieval applications. 

Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves the use of machine learning techniques to optimize user engagement. 

It may also fall under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) as the focus is on improving user engagement in interactive recommender systems. 

Finally, it could be classified under cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it involves the modeling of user behavior in natural language processing.
